WEBVTT

00:02.294 --> 00:03.503
[ Indistinct shouting,
whistle blows ]

00:03.503 --> 00:04.630
All right, class,
substitutions in.

00:04.630 --> 00:06.048
That's you.

00:09.176 --> 00:09.968
Hike!

00:09.968 --> 00:13.680
♪♪

00:16.725 --> 00:19.520
I'm open! I'm open!

00:19.520 --> 00:21.230
I‐I can't see the board,
but that's the gist, right?

00:21.230 --> 00:23.398
Yeah.
Pass the ball!

00:23.398 --> 00:25.817
Pass it!

00:25.817 --> 00:27.694
Oh, no.
She listened.

00:30.739 --> 00:31.698
What?

00:31.698 --> 00:33.200
JJ, run!

00:33.200 --> 00:35.786
Roll, go, whatever.
Just go!

00:35.786 --> 00:37.120
[ Cheers and applause ]
Go!

00:40.040 --> 00:42.709
What ‐‐ What are you doing?
Keep going.

00:44.795 --> 00:45.754
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
Wha‐‐

00:45.754 --> 00:47.172
So no one's coming?

00:47.172 --> 00:48.799
You're just gonna
let him score?

00:48.799 --> 00:51.343
"So P‐A‐‐
patronizing."

00:51.343 --> 00:53.303
Okay, then.
He's coming back.

00:53.303 --> 00:54.888
Pull off a flag
or get run over!

00:54.888 --> 00:56.848
Go on, JJ.

00:56.848 --> 00:58.976
Yeah, you know
who the slow ones are.

01:02.813 --> 01:05.065
♪♪

01:05.065 --> 01:06.858
[ Clicks tongue ] All right.

01:06.858 --> 01:09.361
Done with
my Honors English reading.

01:09.361 --> 01:12.573
And now time
for some pleasure reading.

01:12.573 --> 01:16.201
[ Saxophone playing poorly ]

01:16.201 --> 01:18.579
Since when did you
play saxophone?

01:18.579 --> 01:21.415
Since I found out
it was so loud.

01:21.415 --> 01:22.708
[ Sighs ]

01:24.918 --> 01:26.753
Kenneth! Quick!

01:26.753 --> 01:28.714
There's a man outside,
and he's not breathing.

01:28.714 --> 01:30.007
You've got to come
and do CPR.

01:30.007 --> 01:31.258
Oh, no.
I‐I can't.

01:31.258 --> 01:32.593
I haven't taken
the class yet.

01:32.593 --> 01:34.094
But you promised
you would!

01:34.094 --> 01:36.763
And now a man has died.
Oh, the horror!

01:36.763 --> 01:38.473
You sure there's not
a more dramatic way

01:38.473 --> 01:40.392
to ask if he got
CPR‐certified?

01:40.392 --> 01:42.144
I am being ridiculous
with a purpose.

01:42.144 --> 01:43.353
It is my brand.

01:43.353 --> 01:45.939
You agreed to do that class
immediately.

01:45.939 --> 01:47.482
Now, if you take this job
seriously,

01:47.482 --> 01:48.859
I want to see
one of these.

01:48.859 --> 01:53.113
A tattered CPR card
that expired in 2002?

01:53.113 --> 01:55.073
Oh, help me, Maya!
Oh!

01:55.073 --> 01:57.159
I'm dying in 1998.

01:57.159 --> 01:59.161
How about,
"Neither of us is certified?

01:59.161 --> 02:01.663
Let's go take a class together
and let poor Ray read."

02:01.663 --> 02:04.458
I can't feel my arm.

02:04.458 --> 02:06.626
And "Titanic" is #1
at the box office.

02:06.626 --> 02:08.045
Ugh!

02:08.045 --> 02:09.296
[ Groans ]

02:09.296 --> 02:11.089
So, you made a great play
in football,

02:11.089 --> 02:12.174
and that's a <i>bad</i> thing?

02:14.301 --> 02:21.683
"It was P‐A‐T‐R‐O‐N‐I‐Z‐I‐N‐‐
patronizing."

02:21.683 --> 02:23.852
Oh, I get that.

02:23.852 --> 02:25.145
Hey, am I the one
who takes the longest

02:25.145 --> 02:26.521
to guess which words
you're writing?

02:27.606 --> 02:29.107
Yeah. Hm.

02:30.692 --> 02:34.071
"I don't want pity."

02:35.489 --> 02:37.449
Hey, buddy.
We're kind of having a talk.

02:37.449 --> 02:38.909
Isn't there someplace else
you can go?

02:38.909 --> 02:42.287
I'm trying to go
to a place called <i>me.</i>

02:42.287 --> 02:45.707
[ Door opens, closes ]

02:45.707 --> 02:48.335
"They let me win.

02:48.335 --> 02:53.048
I want to really play.

02:53.048 --> 02:58.679
I want the thrill of C‐O‐M‐P‐‐
competition."

02:59.680 --> 03:02.683
If that's what you want,
I have just the thing.

03:02.683 --> 03:06.061
♪♪

03:09.064 --> 03:10.857
[ Ladder crashes ]
Ray: Help!

03:10.857 --> 03:12.567
Jimmy:
You want to really compete?

03:12.567 --> 03:15.821
No pity, no mercy?
Careful what you wish for.

03:15.821 --> 03:19.616
Who needs sports?
<i>This</i> has everything you need.

03:19.616 --> 03:21.952
Table top,
so it's perfect JJ height.

03:21.952 --> 03:24.621
Joystick ‐‐ think you know
your way around one of those.

03:24.621 --> 03:27.541
If there is a more thrilling
form of competition

03:27.541 --> 03:30.293
for a young man in a wheelchair,
this guy hasn't seen it.

03:33.130 --> 03:34.548
Wait.
We were gonna...

03:34.548 --> 03:36.508
Let's go, guys.
Josh, start us out.

03:40.345 --> 03:43.056
"Do you see this?"

03:46.726 --> 03:49.771
♪♪

03:52.524 --> 03:56.695
[ Both scream ]

03:58.905 --> 04:01.741
So, a few questions.

04:01.741 --> 04:02.617
What the hell?

04:02.617 --> 04:03.869
Why, God, why?

04:03.869 --> 04:05.829
I need a new loofah.

04:05.829 --> 04:07.080
That's more
of a statement.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.540
I‐I am so sorry.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.917
It's just that JJ and I had
been running around all day,

04:10.917 --> 04:11.877
and I got sweaty.

04:11.877 --> 04:13.295
Now, normally,

04:13.295 --> 04:15.338
I'd just go to the gym
and take a shower, but ‐‐

04:15.338 --> 04:17.090
I'm sorry.
Is this an incantation

04:17.090 --> 04:18.842
that will make me unsee
your everything?

04:18.842 --> 04:20.510
It's not.
Okay, then.

04:20.510 --> 04:22.596
I think a conversation about
professionalism needs to happen.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.473
And this is related
to the shower incident?

04:24.473 --> 04:25.807
Directly, yes, yes.
Oh.

04:25.807 --> 04:27.017
I feel you're getting
too comfortable.

04:27.017 --> 04:28.685
I've noticed
a pattern of late.

04:28.685 --> 04:31.688
Failure to take CPR,
some tardiness.

04:31.688 --> 04:32.773
The missing lasagna.

04:32.773 --> 04:33.940
The missing lasagna?

04:33.940 --> 04:36.526
Oh, no, that's my cute,
uh, nickname

04:36.526 --> 04:38.737
for the shower thing.

04:38.737 --> 04:40.530
Mm. At any rate,

04:40.530 --> 04:42.741
it appears it bears reminding
this is a job.

04:42.741 --> 04:45.327
And assuming you wish for it
to remain <i>your</i> job,

04:45.327 --> 04:47.162
kindly treat it as such.

04:47.162 --> 04:49.372
Wait.
Are you being for real?

04:49.372 --> 04:51.875
You actually, like,
got extra British there.

04:51.875 --> 04:52.584
Well,
that's not possible.

04:54.377 --> 04:55.837
Got it.
Understood.

04:55.837 --> 04:58.131
Thank you, Kenneth.

04:58.131 --> 04:59.883
We have to get
to our CPR class.

04:59.883 --> 05:01.301
First,
I must take my shower.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.345
Okay, and if we're
being professional,

05:03.345 --> 05:05.847
I'd like to just state
that the conditioner was gone

05:05.847 --> 05:06.932
before I got in that room.

05:06.932 --> 05:09.935
And if we're being
very professional...

05:09.935 --> 05:11.686
that was a lie.

05:11.686 --> 05:14.189
♪♪

05:22.739 --> 05:24.074
Ray: What the...

05:31.581 --> 05:33.625
I found it.

05:33.625 --> 05:35.085
A place called me.

05:35.085 --> 05:38.255
[ Coughs ]

05:38.255 --> 05:40.173
You never heard
of sled hockey?

05:40.173 --> 05:41.633
It's the most popular
Paralympic sport.

05:41.633 --> 05:42.968
Guys love it.

05:42.968 --> 05:44.427
Feels good, right?

05:44.427 --> 05:46.429
Look at you ‐‐
like a regular Steve Cash.

05:46.429 --> 05:49.099
The famous
sled‐hockey player?

05:49.099 --> 05:50.559
Can't get anything past you,
huh?

05:50.559 --> 05:52.894
Or Steve Cash,
'cause he a goalie, maybe?

05:52.894 --> 05:54.145
Okay.

05:54.145 --> 05:55.939
So, what do you say,
JJ, my man?

05:55.939 --> 05:57.732
You want to get in there
and mix it up a little bit?

05:57.732 --> 05:58.984
All right,
that's what I like to see.

05:58.984 --> 06:00.610
Ha!
[ Chuckles ]

06:00.610 --> 06:01.778
Quick question.

06:01.778 --> 06:04.239
Uh [sighs]

06:04.239 --> 06:06.074
JJ's never done anything
like this before.

06:06.074 --> 06:07.242
Are you sure it's safe?

06:07.242 --> 06:08.785
Oh, absolutely.

06:08.785 --> 06:10.287
Hold up.

06:10.287 --> 06:12.914
Leg time‐out.

06:12.914 --> 06:16.042
Real ones
usually stay on.

06:16.042 --> 06:17.961
♪♪

06:22.632 --> 06:23.925
You're very quiet.

06:23.925 --> 06:25.260
Who?

06:25.260 --> 06:26.636
I know you don't want
to hear from <i>me.</i>

06:26.636 --> 06:29.180
I'm sorry if I was
a little short earlier,

06:29.180 --> 06:30.307
but if you're
gonna get upset

06:30.307 --> 06:31.892
every time
I threaten to fire you,

06:31.892 --> 06:33.560
I'm gonna
have to let you go.

06:34.686 --> 06:35.562
Oh, come on.

06:38.398 --> 06:39.691
Intercepted!

06:39.691 --> 06:41.234
[ Both chuckle ]

06:41.234 --> 06:42.444
I'm Darren.

06:42.444 --> 06:43.945
Nice catch, my man.
Kenneth.

06:43.945 --> 06:45.071
Thank you.
This is my wife, Amanda.

06:45.071 --> 06:46.114
‐Hello.
‐Hey.

06:46.114 --> 06:47.032
And ‐‐ And
your wife is...?

06:47.032 --> 06:48.033
Um...
His boss.

06:48.033 --> 06:48.992
Kenneth works
with my son.

06:51.077 --> 06:52.495
Perfect abdominal thrusts,
Kenneth.

06:52.495 --> 06:54.998
And your form ‐‐
so tender.

06:54.998 --> 06:55.999
Well, thank you.

06:55.999 --> 06:57.500
I think of the Heimlich

06:57.500 --> 06:59.294
as an act of love between
two consenting adults,

06:59.294 --> 07:01.630
one of whom is choking.

07:01.630 --> 07:03.465
You're making
the rest of us look bad.

07:03.465 --> 07:05.967
[ Chuckles ] I'm kidding, man.
Much love.

07:05.967 --> 07:07.469
Don't judge yourself
against this.

07:07.469 --> 07:09.137
I, uh ‐‐
I'm a professional aide.

07:09.137 --> 07:10.138
Amanda: Really?

07:10.138 --> 07:11.640
We've been
thinking about

07:11.640 --> 07:13.850
getting a full‐time aide
for our little boy.

07:13.850 --> 07:15.352
Okay.
Better, Maya.

07:15.352 --> 07:17.103
Not quite as good as Kenneth,
but getting there.

07:19.189 --> 07:20.523
I don't suppose
you have a twin, Kenneth.

07:20.523 --> 07:22.942
Aside from
Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson.

07:22.942 --> 07:24.653
[ Laughter ]
Oh, you.

07:24.653 --> 07:27.155
I must say,
it feels nice to be <i>wanted.</i>

07:27.155 --> 07:29.532
Oh, please.

07:29.532 --> 07:31.743
So strong.
Yeah.

07:31.743 --> 07:32.869
Who wouldn't
want you?

07:32.869 --> 07:34.454
It's a crazy world
we live in, huh?

07:34.454 --> 07:36.373
[ Thudding ]

07:37.707 --> 07:39.417
Maya, stop.
That's enough.

07:39.417 --> 07:41.211
Fine. Let him die.

07:41.211 --> 07:42.212
Her fault.

07:42.212 --> 07:45.173
♪♪

07:45.173 --> 07:48.176
♪ How lucky can one guy be? ♪

07:48.176 --> 07:49.928
Which TED Talk should I watch?

07:49.928 --> 07:52.430
♪ I kissed her
and she kissed me ♪

07:52.430 --> 07:54.683
♪ Like a fella once said ♪
Play all.

07:54.683 --> 07:57.143
♪ "Ain't that a kick
in the head?" ♪
[ Sighs ] I love my life.

08:00.605 --> 08:02.357
You ready for this, JJ?

08:02.357 --> 08:03.650
Okay,
I talked to Coach Barry,

08:03.650 --> 08:05.235
and I think you're gonna
be pretty pleased.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.738
Good job, water boy.

08:08.738 --> 08:11.282
You done this before?

08:12.575 --> 08:13.952
What?

08:13.952 --> 08:16.663
You're part of the team ‐‐
a big part.

08:16.663 --> 08:18.331
They go out there thirsty,
they've already lost.

08:19.416 --> 08:21.126
JJ, where you going?

08:21.126 --> 08:23.128
That kid just
smacked his lips.

08:23.128 --> 08:24.713
That means he's thirsty.

08:24.713 --> 08:26.089
[ Buzzer ]

08:28.186 --> 08:30.427
I don't understand
why you're mad at me.

08:30.427 --> 08:32.345
If anything,
I should be mad at <i>you.</i>

08:32.345 --> 08:34.305
Introduce you to "Ms. Pac‐Man,"
you just blow her off.

08:34.305 --> 08:35.932
That's gonna be
fun phone call tomorrow.

08:37.058 --> 08:40.395
"It's gym class all over.

08:40.395 --> 08:45.775
You treat me like a F‐R‐‐
fragile flower."

08:45.775 --> 08:47.569
What's wrong?

08:47.569 --> 08:50.238
We went to ice rink to play
a nice game of "Ms. Pac‐Man."

08:50.238 --> 08:52.657
There were
some disabled guys on sleds

08:52.657 --> 08:55.326
playing this really
intense game of hockey.

08:55.326 --> 08:56.745
JJ wanted to join in.

08:56.745 --> 08:57.996
Fantastic.
How was it?

08:57.996 --> 09:02.375
"I wasn't
allowed to play."

09:02.375 --> 09:03.793
Who said you couldn't play?
I want a name.

09:03.793 --> 09:05.128
Does it start with "B"?
I'm getting a "B."

09:05.128 --> 09:07.338
I get very psychic
in the presence of injustice.

09:09.257 --> 09:10.258
You?

09:10.258 --> 09:11.801
I thought
you'd agree with me.

09:11.801 --> 09:13.636
I figured you do
your overprotective thing.

09:13.636 --> 09:14.929
No, sir.

09:14.929 --> 09:16.973
This is my
"do not exclude my son,

09:16.973 --> 09:18.308
he can do anything" thing.

09:18.308 --> 09:20.060
Oh, that's the bad one.

09:20.060 --> 09:21.644
Of course he can play
sled hockey.

09:21.644 --> 09:23.730
You didn't let JJ
play sled hockey?

09:23.730 --> 09:26.191
Okay, this is a sport we didn't
know existed this afternoon.

09:26.191 --> 09:29.360
It was like <i>hockey</i> hockey!
He could get hurt.

09:29.360 --> 09:31.321
I get hurt playing sports
all the time.

09:31.321 --> 09:32.906
At a meet last week,
I got decapitated.

09:32.906 --> 09:33.823
That's not ‐‐
No, you weren't.

09:33.823 --> 09:35.200
You weren't there.

09:35.200 --> 09:36.493
I'm pretty sure you're ‐‐
Okay.

09:36.493 --> 09:38.828
Everybody gets hurt.
Why shouldn't JJ?

09:38.828 --> 09:40.038
Because he's different?

09:40.038 --> 09:41.247
Can you go somewhere?

09:41.247 --> 09:42.749
Are you saying
my son's different?

09:42.749 --> 09:44.084
Did I say "different"?

09:44.084 --> 09:45.418
"Implied."
Yeah.

09:47.504 --> 09:49.172
I'm sorry.
I was wrong.

09:49.172 --> 09:50.799
Of course
you're not different.

09:50.799 --> 09:52.383
He's not, okay?

09:52.383 --> 09:54.719
Now, can I have a second
with your mom?

09:54.719 --> 09:56.221
I <i>did</i> get decapitated.

09:56.221 --> 09:58.473
I believe it.
It explains a lot.

09:58.473 --> 09:59.516
Okay.

09:59.516 --> 10:02.227
All that talk, whatever.

10:02.227 --> 10:03.269
He's different.

10:03.269 --> 10:05.855
It's a league
for kids just like him.

10:05.855 --> 10:07.232
Is he different
from them?

10:07.232 --> 10:08.525
Yes.
How?

10:08.525 --> 10:09.442
He's mine.

10:10.860 --> 10:14.239
Everything he's been through ‐‐
what, like 20 surgeries?

10:14.239 --> 10:15.865
Do we need to bash him
into other kids?

10:15.865 --> 10:17.617
That's what's missing
from his life?

10:17.617 --> 10:20.245
Jimmy, there is a whole world
full of people

10:20.245 --> 10:21.329
who will tell him
what he can't do.

10:21.329 --> 10:22.413
That is covered.

10:22.413 --> 10:23.873
Our job is
to tell him otherwise.

10:27.544 --> 10:28.837
That is our job.

10:31.506 --> 10:34.968
And, you know, hey,
if he gets injured,

10:34.968 --> 10:36.177
you and Kenneth
know CPR.

10:36.177 --> 10:38.429
Yeah, about Kenneth.

10:38.429 --> 10:42.517
There's a couple at CPR ‐‐
I think they want to steal him.

10:42.517 --> 10:43.643
They can offer him things
we can't.

10:43.643 --> 10:44.686
Money?

10:44.686 --> 10:46.104
Worse ‐‐ kindness.

10:46.104 --> 10:47.021
Mm.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.731
If we're gonna
keep Kenneth,

10:48.731 --> 10:50.483
I'm gonna have
to be nice to him.

10:50.483 --> 10:51.818
Well...

10:51.818 --> 10:54.904
he will be missed.

10:54.904 --> 10:56.489
♪♪

10:56.489 --> 10:59.450
Hello, Kenneth.
Aren't you looking dapper?

10:59.450 --> 11:01.035
What?
'Cause I got a shirt on?

11:01.035 --> 11:02.745
I‐I get it.
I'm ‐‐ I'm better in clothes.

11:02.745 --> 11:04.164
Not what I meant.

11:04.164 --> 11:06.833
But it occurs to me ‐‐
I did see you nude,

11:06.833 --> 11:08.418
and it was rude of me
not to comment.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.503
Yeah, well, the silence
was deafening.

11:10.503 --> 11:13.339
A long‐overdue kudos.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.341
Here, have a cupcake.

11:15.341 --> 11:17.218
They say "Kenneth."

11:17.218 --> 11:20.054
And I say
Kenneth is great.

11:20.054 --> 11:22.265
Got a "K."
It does, yeah.

11:22.265 --> 11:25.018
So, tell me.

11:25.018 --> 11:27.228
What's new with you?

11:30.106 --> 11:31.357
There's a reason
why I'm looking so good.

11:31.357 --> 11:32.525
Hm?

11:32.525 --> 11:34.277
I just broke up
with my ex.
Oh.

11:34.277 --> 11:36.237
Hence the revenge bod.
Mm.

11:36.237 --> 11:37.697
She texted me the other day,
Tracey did.

11:37.697 --> 11:38.823
Stop it, she didn't.

11:38.823 --> 11:40.116
Yeah,
she's got this new guy.

11:40.116 --> 11:41.951
Does she?
Flashy. Money.

11:41.951 --> 11:43.411
You know,
why do <i>I</i> need to know this?

11:43.411 --> 11:45.205
I don't know.
Because she wants to win.

11:45.205 --> 11:45.955
She wants to win.

11:45.955 --> 11:47.332
But I don't want to play
the game anymore.

11:47.332 --> 11:48.333
No, don't play the game.

11:48.333 --> 11:50.001
I just need
to shut this down.

11:50.001 --> 11:52.754
Not to hurt her.
Just to say, "Enough."
Enough.

11:52.754 --> 11:53.922
"Tracey, you do you.

11:53.922 --> 11:55.131
I'm doing Kenneth."
"I'm doing Kenneth."

11:55.131 --> 11:57.050
All right, class,
let's get started.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.509
To be continued.

11:58.509 --> 11:59.636
Better be.

11:59.636 --> 12:00.595
[ Chuckles ]

12:04.891 --> 12:06.726
All right, see, JJ?

12:06.726 --> 12:08.937
We're getting in there,
we're mixing it up.

12:08.937 --> 12:10.605
Whoa, close one.

12:10.605 --> 12:12.273
Oh, oh.

12:12.273 --> 12:13.900
Over here.
Coming to you.

12:13.900 --> 12:14.692
No, we don't want it.

12:14.692 --> 12:15.735
That guy's open.

12:17.237 --> 12:18.321
[ Sighs ]

12:18.321 --> 12:19.155
Nice.

12:20.531 --> 12:21.366
Wha‐‐

12:22.659 --> 12:25.245
All right,
let's do this.

12:25.245 --> 12:29.916
[ Motorhead's "Ace Of Spades"
plays ]

12:29.916 --> 12:31.334
Brace for impact!

12:31.334 --> 12:32.877
Oh!

12:32.877 --> 12:34.921
That wasn't so bad.

12:36.089 --> 12:38.007
Loose puck.

12:38.007 --> 12:40.176
♪ If you like to gamble,
I tell you I'm your man ♪
Come on, JJ.

12:40.176 --> 12:41.594
It's all yours.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.096
♪ You win some, lose some ♪
Come on, come on.

12:43.096 --> 12:44.597
♪ It's all the same to me ♪
Yeah!

12:44.597 --> 12:45.765
All right.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.016
Do we say something
to him?

12:47.016 --> 12:49.102
Uh, uh,
maybe we own him?

12:49.102 --> 12:51.437
We own you.
Good job, JJ.

12:51.437 --> 12:53.273
♪ The pleasure is to play ♪

12:53.273 --> 12:54.941
♪ It makes no difference
what you say ♪

12:58.319 --> 12:59.696
♪ <i>I don't share your greed</i> ♪
'Sup, Ray?

12:59.696 --> 13:01.531
♪ <i>The only card I need is</i>
<i>The Ace Of Spades</i> ♪

13:01.531 --> 13:03.241
What are you
doing in here?
[ Music stops ]

13:03.241 --> 13:04.867
You shouldn't have been
so careless.

13:04.867 --> 13:06.744
I could smell your candles
from the front yard.

13:06.744 --> 13:09.330
You can't be here.
This is my place.

13:09.330 --> 13:11.708
I need it to relax
and contemplate

13:11.708 --> 13:13.876
and process
my fears and emotions.

13:13.876 --> 13:15.586
So I read.

13:15.586 --> 13:16.671
Yeesh.

13:16.671 --> 13:18.256
Take your pizza,

13:18.256 --> 13:19.716
mention my dream about Mom
to no one,

13:19.716 --> 13:21.009
and get out of my space.

13:21.009 --> 13:22.385
Share it with me,

13:22.385 --> 13:24.304
or that journal
goes up on the cloud.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.347
A place called us
it is.

13:28.641 --> 13:30.476
Psst, Ken.
Hmm?

13:30.476 --> 13:31.728
Hey.

13:31.728 --> 13:33.229
I just want to apologize

13:33.229 --> 13:35.189
if we caused any trouble
with your boss.

13:35.189 --> 13:37.358
[ Chuckles ]
What are you talking about?

13:37.358 --> 13:41.029
Well, before class, she told us,
stay away, you're taken.

13:43.406 --> 13:45.366
You don't say.

13:45.366 --> 13:47.493
Huh.

13:47.493 --> 13:50.747
Suddenly, these cupcakes
got a lot less appetizing.

13:54.375 --> 13:57.754
♪♪

13:57.754 --> 13:58.629
You having fun?

13:58.629 --> 14:00.465
Yeah, me too.

14:00.465 --> 14:02.592
You know, I was never really
much of an athlete as a child.

14:02.592 --> 14:03.885
Oh!

14:03.885 --> 14:04.802
You know what?
Later.

14:04.802 --> 14:06.095
We got a game to play.

14:07.638 --> 14:09.182
What?
Right, back on defense.

14:09.182 --> 14:10.600
Let's do this.

14:10.600 --> 14:13.561
Block, block,
block, block!

14:14.353 --> 14:15.188
Oh.

14:16.773 --> 14:18.191
Is that your t‐‐

14:18.191 --> 14:19.692
Dentist.
Dentist.

14:19.692 --> 14:20.943
Dentist.
Dentist!

14:23.067 --> 14:26.032
♪♪

14:26.032 --> 14:27.200
[ <i>Sports chatter</i>
<i>on television</i> ]
Kenneth.

14:27.200 --> 14:28.117
Hey.

14:28.117 --> 14:29.368
JJ's not even here.

14:29.368 --> 14:30.369
No.

14:30.369 --> 14:31.412
[ Television shuts off ]

14:31.412 --> 14:32.663
But my buddy is.

14:32.663 --> 14:33.706
Ah.
[ Chuckles ]

14:33.706 --> 14:35.166
By the way,
uh, you are out

14:35.166 --> 14:37.835
of bagels, cream cheese,
tomatoes, and bandages.

14:37.835 --> 14:40.296
Uh, I'm not that good
at cutting bagels.

14:40.296 --> 14:41.255
[ Chuckles ]

14:41.255 --> 14:44.217
What's mine
is yours... buddy.

14:44.217 --> 14:46.719
So, I'm guessing you are wanting
the latest chapter

14:46.719 --> 14:48.513
in the saga with my ex.

14:48.513 --> 14:50.640
Want?
Try <i>need.</i>

14:50.640 --> 14:51.933
[ Chuckles ]

14:51.933 --> 14:54.352
So, I'm having this dream
about Tracey last night,

14:54.352 --> 14:55.770
and we are in a boat

14:55.770 --> 14:58.481
in the middle of ‐‐ get this ‐‐
the ocean.

14:58.481 --> 15:00.733
What?
Mind... blown.

15:00.733 --> 15:03.778
Yeah, and we're having
a fantasy‐football draft.

15:03.778 --> 15:05.988
And my running backs
are DeAngelo Williams,

15:05.988 --> 15:07.657
Jeremy Hill,
and Julius Thomas.

15:07.657 --> 15:09.283
But crazy thing is,
in real life,

15:09.283 --> 15:11.035
Julius Thomas
is a tight end.

15:11.035 --> 15:12.370
Is he? Wow.

15:12.370 --> 15:16.457
What a fascinating story
to tell while barefoot.

15:16.457 --> 15:19.127
So, after the draft, I'm tired,
and so I take a nap.

15:19.127 --> 15:22.171
And then I have a dream
in my dream!

15:22.171 --> 15:23.256
Oh, I can't
take it anymore!

15:23.256 --> 15:24.549
I hate hearing about
people's dreams.

15:24.549 --> 15:25.967
I know.

15:25.967 --> 15:27.760
You told me once,
and I listened.

15:27.760 --> 15:29.262
I care.

15:29.262 --> 15:31.055
Unlike you,
who's just pretending to

15:31.055 --> 15:33.224
because you're afraid
that that CPR couple
will steal me away.

15:33.224 --> 15:34.725
They told you about that,
did they?

15:34.725 --> 15:36.978
[ Voice breaking ] Did they also
tell you how I teared up

15:36.978 --> 15:38.354
at the thought
of losing you

15:38.354 --> 15:40.731
and how I've come
to think of you

15:40.731 --> 15:42.233
as the brother
that I never had?

15:43.276 --> 15:45.236
[ Normal voice ]
Fine. Too Far.

15:45.236 --> 15:47.155
You bug me!

15:47.155 --> 15:49.240
I only put up with you
'cause I care about JJ.

15:49.240 --> 15:50.741
Yeah, right back at you.

15:56.622 --> 15:57.331
[ Thud ]

15:58.416 --> 16:00.918
No. Don't.

16:00.918 --> 16:02.962
Wait, what happened
to the saxophone?

16:02.962 --> 16:04.755
Doesn't fit
in my practice space.

16:04.755 --> 16:07.175
And I'm a lot better
at this.

16:07.175 --> 16:08.384
[ Sour notes play ]

16:08.384 --> 16:09.719
Okay, okay, that's it.

16:09.719 --> 16:11.220
That's it.
You have to leave.

16:11.220 --> 16:13.347
Or what?
Are you gonna journal about it?

16:13.347 --> 16:15.808
I would be
well within my rights.

16:15.808 --> 16:18.811
I can't have my little sister
around all the time.

16:18.811 --> 16:20.313
I need my privacy.

16:20.313 --> 16:22.023
<i>You</i> do?
[ Scoffs ]

16:22.023 --> 16:23.441
You think it's easy
sharing a bedroom

16:23.441 --> 16:24.775
with your two
older brothers?

16:24.775 --> 16:26.402
I can't change
in my own room.

16:26.402 --> 16:28.112
I can't get any of
my girlfriends to come over,

16:28.112 --> 16:29.530
let alone any dudes.

16:29.530 --> 16:31.073
Gross!
Well, it's true.

16:31.073 --> 16:33.034
You're not the only one
who needs privacy, Ray.

16:33.034 --> 16:35.036
You're just the one who
complains about it the most.

16:37.455 --> 16:40.166
Why do you think
I need to play the blues?

16:41.375 --> 16:44.545
[ Sour notes play ]

16:44.545 --> 16:45.880
Right.

16:45.880 --> 16:47.798
Until JJ gets
his tooth repaired,

16:47.798 --> 16:50.051
there will be no solid food
at this table.

16:50.051 --> 16:52.970
Just
instant mashed potatoes.

16:52.970 --> 16:54.472
My teeth
didn't get knocked out.

16:54.472 --> 16:55.723
Not yet, they didn't.

16:55.723 --> 16:57.433
Now, listen to Mom
and eat your gruel.

16:57.433 --> 16:59.393
Didn't know
it was gonna be so violent.

16:59.393 --> 17:00.770
Wasn't it just a practice?

17:00.770 --> 17:02.813
Can't wait to see
what the game is like.

17:02.813 --> 17:07.401
"I can't make the game."

17:07.401 --> 17:08.819
Why?

17:10.947 --> 17:12.281
What?
You want to quit?

17:12.281 --> 17:16.035
"I'm a lover,
not a fighter."

17:16.035 --> 17:16.786
Oh, Ray,
don't say "lover."

17:16.786 --> 17:18.287
<i>He</i> said it!

17:18.287 --> 17:20.331
I understand you got hurt
and it was scary,

17:20.331 --> 17:22.458
but this is what
you wanted.

17:22.458 --> 17:24.835
Jimmy, leave him alone.
He's been disfigured.

17:24.835 --> 17:27.004
On a scale from 1 to 10,
he's down to a 13.

17:27.004 --> 17:27.964
But you don't give up,
right?

17:30.591 --> 17:31.676
Am I the only one
who sees this?

17:33.636 --> 17:36.055
You are not quitting.

17:36.055 --> 17:38.224
I saw something
you didn't.

17:38.224 --> 17:41.686
How... happy you were
out there.

17:41.686 --> 17:43.187
I've never seen you
like that.

17:44.939 --> 17:47.900
"But I broke my face.

17:47.900 --> 17:49.277
You were right."

17:49.277 --> 17:51.362
Hey, you got hurt,

17:51.362 --> 17:53.239
but not because
you have cerebral palsy.

17:53.239 --> 17:55.866
You got hurt because
you were playing hockey.

17:57.159 --> 17:58.744
I don't know much
about sports.

17:58.744 --> 18:02.373
But I know a thing or two about
movies about sports,

18:02.373 --> 18:06.252
and in them, somebody always
stands up and starts yelling

18:06.252 --> 18:10.339
about digging deep
and drunk dads

18:10.339 --> 18:12.842
and this town needs
something to cheer for

18:12.842 --> 18:13.884
now that
the factory's gone.

18:13.884 --> 18:16.637
Imagine that's all true.

18:16.637 --> 18:18.889
Ooh, this is good.

18:18.889 --> 18:21.726
You don't like people clapping
and letting you win?

18:21.726 --> 18:25.229
No one is giving you anything
out there.

18:25.229 --> 18:28.357
It's yours to grab.

18:28.357 --> 18:30.192
Take it.

18:30.192 --> 18:31.611
You're in?

18:31.611 --> 18:33.279
Yeah.

18:33.279 --> 18:36.240
Ooh, I'm in, too, now!
I love it!

18:36.240 --> 18:37.450
Feels like a good time
to tell you

18:37.450 --> 18:40.536
that we actually lost
our dental insurance.

18:42.163 --> 18:43.039
[ Knock on door ]

18:43.039 --> 18:44.999
Hello, Kenneth.

18:44.999 --> 18:46.459
I'm not taking
another job,

18:46.459 --> 18:48.210
so you don't have
to pretend to be nice.

18:48.210 --> 18:49.629
Just follow me,
would you?

18:49.629 --> 18:50.671
I'll follow you,

18:50.671 --> 18:52.340
but I'm gonna need to see
your hands the whole way.

18:54.175 --> 18:55.843
Well, I've got something
to show you.

18:55.843 --> 18:58.137
Uh, o‐open that.

19:01.724 --> 19:03.559
It's empty.

19:03.559 --> 19:05.144
Good one?

19:05.144 --> 19:07.229
It's for you ‐‐
to hold your things,

19:07.229 --> 19:08.481
for when
you shower here.

19:08.481 --> 19:10.066
But it bothers you
when I shower here.

19:10.066 --> 19:10.983
It does.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.943
But I realized

19:12.943 --> 19:14.695
you've earned a certain amount
of bothering me.

19:16.489 --> 19:19.367
Wow, that's...actually
pretty nice.

19:19.367 --> 19:20.743
And not in a fake way.

19:20.743 --> 19:23.454
This, uh, works.

19:23.454 --> 19:25.831
I may not like
everything you do.

19:25.831 --> 19:28.209
I certainly did not need
to see you naked.

19:28.209 --> 19:30.586
But it's far better
to see you naked

19:30.586 --> 19:32.046
than to not see you
at all.

19:34.340 --> 19:35.549
I'm starting
to like you, too.

19:38.636 --> 19:39.970
Look at you two.
[ Gasps ]

19:39.970 --> 19:41.806
You have come so far.

19:41.806 --> 19:43.432
Please hand me a towel
and leave.

19:43.432 --> 19:45.309
It is not your turn
for the towel, Ray.

19:48.145 --> 19:49.605
It's right there!

19:49.605 --> 19:52.900
[ Cheering ]

19:52.900 --> 19:54.568
Kenneth:
Let's go, DiMeo!

19:55.611 --> 19:57.279
These guys
are really good.

19:57.279 --> 19:58.572
Yeah, but he's out there
doing it.

19:58.572 --> 20:00.032
Go, JJ!

20:00.032 --> 20:01.992
Come on, JJ!

20:01.992 --> 20:03.369
Did you use
my deodorant?

20:03.369 --> 20:05.329
I'm not gonna lie.
I‐I did.

20:05.329 --> 20:06.247
It's nice, isn't it?

20:06.247 --> 20:07.540
Mm‐hmm.

20:07.540 --> 20:09.875
Oh, come on, ref!
You gonna call that?!

20:09.875 --> 20:11.502
Oh, the ref
isn't disabled, is he?

20:11.502 --> 20:12.670
No.

20:12.670 --> 20:13.838
Die, ref!

20:13.838 --> 20:16.173
Hey,
how amazing is this?

20:17.758 --> 20:19.635
Doing a sport with my son!

20:19.635 --> 20:21.137
Mm, mm.

20:21.137 --> 20:21.929
Do the sport.

20:21.929 --> 20:23.973
Oh, God.

20:23.973 --> 20:25.224
Let's go.
Whoo!

20:25.224 --> 20:26.434
[ Whistles ]

20:26.434 --> 20:27.893
Kenneth: Let's go!

20:27.893 --> 20:29.353
Come on, Jimmy!

20:29.353 --> 20:31.647
Man: JJ, look behind you!

20:33.816 --> 20:35.443
They're coming, man!
They're coming!

20:35.443 --> 20:37.278
JJ, they're coming!

20:37.278 --> 20:38.112
[ Cheering ]

20:41.196 --> 20:43.784
Hey, Dylan.
We need to talk.

20:43.784 --> 20:44.869
Yesterday in the shower,

20:44.869 --> 20:46.787
I was moved by a gesture
Mom made for Kenneth.

20:46.787 --> 20:48.831
That sounds like
primo journal stuff.

20:48.831 --> 20:50.207
Take a look at this.

20:53.502 --> 20:55.337
You deserve
some space, too.

20:55.337 --> 20:56.672
We'll take turns.

20:56.672 --> 20:58.632
You get Tuesday, Thursday,
and Friday afternoons,

20:58.632 --> 21:00.342
but every other weekend
we switch off.

21:00.342 --> 21:02.136
Every third Thursday
of the month is mine,

21:02.136 --> 21:04.096
and every second Sunday
of the month is yours.

21:04.096 --> 21:05.848
You did this all today?

21:05.848 --> 21:08.893
I drew this up years ago in case
Mom and Dad ever got a divorce.

21:08.893 --> 21:10.144
It converted perfectly.

21:10.144 --> 21:11.562
Thanks, Ray.

21:13.898 --> 21:15.733
Want to go in there together
one last time?

21:15.733 --> 21:17.526
I'd like that.

21:17.526 --> 21:21.489
♪♪

21:21.489 --> 21:23.282
This was a weird idea.

21:23.282 --> 21:24.033
Let's go.
